re becoming realities thanks to the visionary efforts of scientists to reveal the invisible and secret universe within each of us. Focusing on six important frontiers, Davis describes what we are learning about cells, the development of the fetus, the body's immune system, the brain, the microbiome, and the genome—areas of human biology that are usually understood in isolation. Bringing them together here for the first time, Davis offers a new vision of the human body as a biological wonder of dizzying complexity and possibility.Written by an award-winning scientist at the forefront of this adventure, The Secret Body is a gripping drama of discovery and a landmark account of the dawning revolution in human health.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aHuman biologyvPopular works. 0aMedical innovations. 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Biology.2bisacsh  aAllergy.  aAntibody.  aAntonie van Leeuwenhoek.  aB cell.  aBacteria.  aBiology.  aBiopsy.  aBiotechnology.  aBrainbow.  aBreast cancer.  aCRISPR.  aCamillo Golgi.  aCancer cell.  aCarcinogen.  aChemotherapy.  aChorionic villus sampling.  aChédiak–Higashi syndrome.  aClinical trial.  aClinical trials registry.  aClostridium difficile colitis.  aCraig Venter.  aCystic fibrosis.  aDieting.  aDisease.  aDown syndrome.  aEileen Southgate.  aElectron microscope.  aElevated plus maze.  aEmbryo.  aErnst Abbe.  aFlow cytometry.  aFrancis Crick.  aFunctional magnetic resonance imaging.  aGenetic testing.  aGlucose.  aGut flora.  aHIV.  aHilary Koprowski.  aHuman Genome Project.  aHuman Longevity Inc.  aHuman body.  aHuman genome.  aHydrodynamic focusing.  aHygiene hypothesis.  aImmortalised cell line.  aImmunology.  aIn vitro fertilisation.  aIn vitro.  aInception.  aIntracytoplasmic sp